net.objectzoo.events.impl

Interface Event3AsyncDelegate<T1,T2,T3>

  • Type Parameters:
    T1 - The type of the first information parameter the event provides
    T2 - The type of the second information parameter the event provides
    T3 - The type of the third information parameter the event provides
    All Superinterfaces:
    Action3<T1,T2,T3>, Action3Async<T1,T2,T3>, Event3<T1,T2,T3>, Event3Delegate<T1,T2,T3>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Event3AsyncAdapter

    public interface Event3AsyncDelegate<T1,T2,T3>
extends Action3Async<T1,T2,T3>, Event3Delegate<T1,T2,T3>
    An Event3AsyncDelegate implements Action3Async as well as Event3Delegate and is meant as a specification for implementations that delegate calls to the Action3Async interface asynchronously to all subscribers of the Event3Delegate interface.

    tilmann
